g.text: Step 1-4: Validate request, extract claims, parse expires_at, generate short_code
Step 5: Build URLCreatedEvent payload (before TX opens — marshal cannot fail inside TX)
Step 6: Single atomic transaction — BOTH rows or NEITHER
Step 6 continued: COMMIT — both rows atomically visible or neither
Async: Outbox poller publishes the event (runs every 2s, independent of HTTP)

text.tspan: WHY TWO SEPARATE TXs WOULD BREAK at-least-once:
→ URL created but no event ever published.
Consumers never notified. Silent data loss.
